===Etymology 1===
Attested somewhat late (in {{w|Warring States period}}'s texts). 

Starostin reconstructs {{och-l|吞|tr=*tʰən}} derives it from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*dhɨ̄ŋ|*dhɨ̄n ~ *dhɨ̄ŋ|to swallow, to drink}}, whence also {{cog|bo|འཐུང||to drink}} & {{cog|lep|tr=thóng|t=to drink}}, which STEDT derives from {{cog|sit-pro|*m/s-tuŋ||to drink, to suckle}}; however, STEDT does not derive {{lang|zh|吞}} from or compare it to {{m|sit-pro|*m/s-tuŋ}}.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares it to several {{w|Kam–Tai languages|Kam-Tai}} words: {{cog|th|กลืน}}, {{cog|aho|tr=k(l)en}}, {{cog|skb|tr=tlɯɯn<sup>A1</sup>}}, {{cog|qfa-kms-pro|*ʔdun}}, etc.

